OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FLinda Razzell: Killer      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fhusband refused parole     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Funder Helen's law          
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A man who has refused to reveal where  
OL,6, the body of his murdered wife is has   
OL,7, had his parole bid turned down under a 
OL,8, new law.                               
OL,10,FGlyn Razzell, from Somerset, is serving
OL,11,Fa life sentence for the murder of his  
OL,12,F41-year-old wife Linda Razzell.        
OL,14,FUnder Helen's Law, it is harder for    
OL,15,Fkillers to get parole if they refuse to
OL,16,Freveal where their victim's bodies are.
OL,18,FRazzell is one of the first prisoners  
OL,19,Fto be considered under the law, which  
OL,20,Fwas enacted in January.                
